  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-07-09",
    "date": "2009-08-05T15:38:34Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax credit for 50% of the non-clinical research expenses for certain infectious diseases or conditions for which there is no significant market in developed nations and which disproportionately affect poor and marginalized populations. Requires any taxpayer who claims this tax credit to donate to a charitable organization or foreign government for public purposes the rights to any license for treatment of such diseases."
  },
